olive oil
½ Brown Onion
2 clove garlic
½ tin sweetcorn
1 carrot
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
⅓ cup water
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet sour cream

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop onion (see ingredients) and garlic.
Drain the sweetcorn (see ingredients). Grate
the carrot.

• Slice each mini flourtortilla into 6 wedges.
Arrange tortilla wedges over two lined oven
trays. Drizzle (or spray) with olive oil and season
with salt and pepper.
• Bake until golden and crispy, 8-10 minutes.

TIP: Keep an eye on them. You want them crisp, but
not burnt!

• While the nacho chips are baking, heat a large
frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook onion, stirring, until softened,
3-4 minutes.
• Add carrot and sweetcorn and cook until
softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and Tex-Mex spice blend and cook
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add beef mince and cook, breaking up with a
spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes.

• Add tomato paste, the water and beef-style
stock powder to the beef and stir to combine.
Bring to the boil, then reduce heat to low and
simmer until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Stir through baby spinach leaves until wilted,
1 minute. Season with pepper.

TIP: Don't simmer it for too long, you want it to be
nice and saucy! Add a dash more water to loosen the mixture if needed.

• Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over beef
mixture, then cover with a lid (or foil) and cook
until cheese has melted, 2-3 minutes.

• Divide nacho chips between plates and top with
cheesy beef mixture.
• Dollop with sour cream to serve. Enjoy!

TIP: Serve the nacho chips on the side if you prefer!